<TITLE> 'Wanted killer' dies in shootout with RAB </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 25 (bdnews24.com)  An alleged killer died after a shootout with Rapid Action Batallion in the capital's Tejgaon industrial area Friday, said RAB in a statement. RAB headquarters claimed that Shaheb Ali (32) was a close associate of top listed terrorist Pichchi Hannan, who used to collect illegal tolls and worked as a professional killer on hire for Hannan in the Karwan Bazar and Tejgaon areas of the city. The elite force in its statement said a team of RAB-2 members challenged Ali and his associates as they were holding a meeting behind a godown near the Tejgaon truck stand early Friday morning. The suspects fired at the RAB men, who retaliated in self defence. After trading shots for around half an hour, the terrorists fled and RAB members found Ali at the spot suffering bullet wounds. Ali was taken to Dhaka Medical College Hospital emergency department where doctors on duty declared him dead. RAB said its men recovered a foreign made revolver, a round of bullets, cartridges and two Nokia cellphone sets from the spot. The statement said there were several cases against Shaheb Ali with different police stations in the capital, including on charges of murder. Shaheb Ali and other associates of Pichchi Hannan were also involved in a gun fight between RAB-1 members in 2005, RAB said. He received a gunshot wound in the leg at that time and later underwent an amputation, with a replacement artificial leg, at a cost of in India, the statement said. Officer-in-charge of Tejgaon police Shafiqul Islam Shikder told bdnews24.com that RAB-2 deputy assistant director Mahmudul Hasan had filed a case in this connection. bdnews
